Six persons, including four children were injured in an accident in Nteje area of Anambra State. The crash which occurred Sunday evening involved a Toyota Corolla car and Coster bus with 15 persons on board. An eyewitness said the crash was caused by an unguarded U-turn on the highway. Sector Commander, Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC), Andrew Kumapayi confirmed the accident, adding that no death was recorded.